Mixed feelings about this app. I have used it for about a month or so. Today, for some reason, it stopped displaying the Google map on the screen, just a blank screen. Although my location and nearby lightning strikes were shown as coloured dots. I deleted the app and reinstalled from the Google Play store, and it has fixed this - the background map is again showing up. But I should not need to have to do this. Was this a glitch with the app or a Google problem? Not sure.
replyContent: Unfortunately this is a bug in the latest version of Google Maps. I believe they are working on a fix. Luckily it only affects a small number of random users. You have already done the recommended solution of uninstalling the app and then installing it again.
